            "len": 1482,
            "post_value": "At Microsoft, I spent the last two years acting as the primary technical counterpart for enterprise partners at Azure scale, leading architecture reviews and recovery engagements with companies like Databricks, Walmart, and SAP. I built a resilience automation platform from 0 to 1, translated fragmented requirements from 140+ distributed teams into a coherent prioritization framework, and served as technical lead on a sovereign-cloud network isolation test tied to a $1.5B+ contract. That work, bridging engineering depth with enterprise sales cycles and stakeholder alignment, maps directly to what this role demands. The OP Stack Solutions Architect role is essentially that same motion applied to blockchain infrastructure, and that overlap is hard to ignore.\n\nWhat draws me specifically to Optimism is the scale and seriousness of the bet. Over 65% of Ethereum Layer 2 activity running through the OP Stack is not a niche experiment, it is becoming the default substrate for onchain financial infrastructure. The institutions OP Labs is bringing onchain, banks, asset managers, exchanges, are exactly the kinds of regulated, high-stakes partners I have experience navigating. I want to be part of the team that makes production-grade deployment on the OP Stack the obvious choice for the next wave of institutional builders, and I think the combination of my enterprise technical program experience and genuine conviction in what OP Labs is building makes this a strong fit."
          }
        ],
