            "len": 1452,
            "post_value": "At Microsoft, I pioneered Azure's first proactive rack-level resilience testing capability from scratch. There was no playbook, no prior infrastructure for it, and significant skepticism about timeline. I delivered the full program in 4 months, achieved a 94% recovery rate, and surfaced critical hardware defects that shaped Azure's long-term platform reliability strategy. On top of that, I served as the bridge lead for a sovereign-cloud network isolation test tied to a $1.5B+ enterprise contract, directing 14 cross-org recovery executions under direct executive visibility while maintaining strict regulatory compliance throughout. Both of those were high-stakes, ambiguous situations where I had to define the approach myself and execute without a safety net.\n\nThe second example goes back to my 2022 internship at Microsoft. I inherited a fragmented automation prioritization process spread across 140+ teams with no unified framework. I drove cross-functional alignment on a single prioritization model, which accelerated region launches by 28% and generated $3M in revenue impact. What made it exceptional wasn't just the outcome - it was that I had to run discovery with 20+ service teams, translate messy operational pain into a clear product direction, and get buy-in across a massive org as an intern. Both examples reflect the same pattern: internalize the problem, design the approach, and deliver results that go beyond what was asked."
          }
