            "len": 1271,
            "post_value": "The most relevant thing I've built is Azure's Resilience Automation Platform - an internal system I took from 0 to 1 at Microsoft. The problem it solved was that recovery validation across Azure's data-heavy, interdependent services was entirely manual and ad hoc. I defined the product requirements, wrote the self-service scheduling specs, and established the adoption criteria that transitioned execution from a hands-on operational model to a scalable, maintainable one. That shift reduced operational toil by 30% and allowed the program to sustain 45+ annual drills without proportional headcount growth.\n\nThe work was deeply cross-functional - I partnered with engineering, data science, and solutions teams to understand how internal systems were actually being used, map the interdependencies, and sequence delivery in a way that didn't break reliability while we were building. I also defined and tracked success metrics across the platform, things like latency, reliability, and stakeholder satisfaction, and communicated roadmap tradeoffs to leadership regularly. That combination of data-heavy technical scope, cross-org dependency management, and internal platform ownership is exactly what this role is asking for, which is a big part of why I'm interested."
