            "len": 1214,
            "post_value": "Healthcare complexity is something I've seen affect people close to me - watching family members struggle to understand what their insurance covers, which specialist to see, or why a claim was denied is genuinely frustrating. The statistic that 88% of adults lack the health literacy to navigate the system on their own doesn't surprise me at all. It matches what I've observed firsthand. The idea that Solace is pairing patients with expert advocates to cut through that red tape is the kind of mission I want to spend my time on.\n\nBeyond the mission, the specific problem Solace is solving maps directly to work I find compelling. At Microsoft, I spent real time diagnosing friction in complex workflows, synthesizing qualitative signals from partner teams into testable hypotheses, and building systems that made hard things more navigable. The funnel Solace is optimizing - from first website visit to a patient showing up for their appointment - is a high-stakes version of exactly that. Every percentage point improvement in booking rate or show rate translates to a real person getting help they needed. That connection between the metric and the human outcome is what makes this role feel worth doing well."
          },
          {
            "id": "4af9d640-24b6-4d96-8dfd-1df5189220fe_0dafdb9b-3804-4ede-bf60-4fd988f72951",
            "dom_id": "0dafdb9b-3804-4ede-bf60-4fd988f72951",
            "len": 1138,
            "post_value": "I don't have a pre-recorded video link to share at this stage, but I'm happy to record and submit one on short notice if that's a requirement for moving forward. In the meantime, here's the substance of what I'd say:\n\nI've spent the last two years at Microsoft running a prioritized experimentation backlog, synthesizing qualitative research from 10+ partner teams into testable hypotheses, and translating results into clear stakeholder recommendations that shaped quarterly roadmap decisions. Before that, at Pro Painters, I directly improved CTR and landing page conversion by optimizing paid and organic channels, reduced customer acquisition cost by 13%, and increased job bookings by 26% by redesigning the intake funnel end to end. That combination - hands-on funnel work, structured experimentation, and qualitative research that drives the test calendar - is exactly what this role calls for.\n\nI'm comfortable working directly in tools like Webflow and Statsig, I move fast without cutting corners on rigor, and I care about the patient experience Solace is building toward. I'd welcome the chance to show that in a conversation."
          }
        ],
