          },
          {
            "id": "4b16c7bc-a2f5-448e-9245-dac2b8c25d93_c2b27edc-aa94-4266-b8fc-9df822f563e4",
            "dom_id": "c2b27edc-aa94-4266-b8fc-9df822f563e4",
            "len": 1367,
            "post_value": "My work at Microsoft has centered on exactly the intersection Talos operates in: building scalable, reliable platforms for high-stakes environments where downtime or coordination failures have real financial consequences. I led 14 cross-org recovery executions under executive visibility, including a sovereign-cloud network isolation test tied to a $1.5B+ enterprise contract, coordinating requirements and release readiness across engineering and client teams. That kind of structured delivery under pressure, paired with sprint coordination, backlog grooming, and building internal tooling that reduced planning cycle time by 39%, maps directly to what the Sell-Side APM role is asking for.What draws me specifically to Talos is the seriousness of the problem. Institutional crypto infrastructure is genuinely hard, and Talos is building the connective tissue that makes the whole ecosystem function for the players who actually matter at scale. The Sell-Side product suite sits at the core of that, and the chance to work at that layer, supporting roadmap execution, client go-lives, and feature delivery in a capital markets context, is the kind of focused, high-signal environment I want to be in. The fact that Talos has built a reputation for trust and rigor in a market that desperately needs both makes this a particularly interesting place to contribute."
          },
          {
            "id": "4b16c7bc-a2f5-448e-9245-dac2b8c25d93_5861cbbf-ed2d-496e-9e8e-c558b67e5130",
            "dom_id": "5861cbbf-ed2d-496e-9e8e-c558b67e5130",
            "len": 1859,
            "post_value": "I want to be straightforward: my direct employment history is in cloud infrastructure and enterprise SaaS rather than a capital markets firm. That said, my most relevant project maps closely to sell-side-grade operational demands, and I think it demonstrates the core skills this role requires.\n\nAt Microsoft, I pioneered Azure's first proactive resilience testing capability for enterprise clients, delivering a rack-level drill program in 4 months with a 94% recovery rate. The clients involved, including Databricks, Walmart, SAP, and NetApp, required the kind of uptime guarantees and structured release discipline that mirror what sell-side trading infrastructure demands. I owned the full delivery lifecycle: defining requirements, coordinating environment readiness, managing configuration alignment across engineering and operations teams, and maintaining structured handover documentation before every production promotion. I also served as bridge lead for a sovereign-cloud network isolation test tied to a $1.5B+ enterprise contract, coordinating cross-functional requirements and release readiness across engineering and client teams under significant executive visibility.\n\nOn the tooling side, I built an internal AI-driven planning agent and restructured sprint workflows that cut planning cycle time by 39% and increased drill capacity by 21%, and I maintained documentation and release notes throughout. I am also a member of a Trading Enthusiast Club and have been actively deepening my understanding of digital asset market structure. While I have not worked inside a capital markets firm, the delivery rigor, API validation, configuration management, and cross-functional coordination I have practiced at Microsoft translate directly to what the Sell-Side APM role is asking for, and I am genuinely motivated to apply them in this context."
          }
        ],
